                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" align="left" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="7" align="left" colwidth="1.34in" colsep="1"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At back of cluster connector (420) measure voltage to ground at circuit 28C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(420) circuit 28C to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of NO or LOW voltage in circuit 28C from 10A fuse F4-A, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At back of cluster connector (420) jumper circuit 40 to ground and note if light
                                    turns ON.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(420)</para>
                                <para>circuit 40 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Light on?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off/On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (460) and (512) from low air pressure switches. KEY ON-
                                    Measure voltage to ground at connector (460) circuit 40A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(460) circuit 40A to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 40/40A between connectors (420) and (460), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (460) measure voltage between circuits 40A and 40-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(460) circuits 40A and 40-GA</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 40-GA between connector (460) and left dash panel ground
                                    stud, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With less than 60 PSI/413.7 KPa air pressure, measure resistance across switch
                                    terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Switch terminals</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the low air pressure switch and go to the next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (512) measure voltage to ground at circuit 40B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(512) circuit 40B to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 40B between connector (512) and (420), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (512) measure voltage between circuits 40B and 40-GB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(512) circuits 40B and 40-GB</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 40-GB, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With less than 60 PSI/413.7 KPa air pressure, measure resistance across switch
                                    terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Switch terminals</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the switch and go to the next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (421) from Speedo/Tach module. Measure voltage to ground at
                                    circuit 40C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(421) circuit 40C to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 40C, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The low air pressure warning light system and alarm circuits check good.*</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>*The alarm should sound short beeps continuously while the low air pressure light is ON. If the alarm
                doesn't sound for low air pressure warning light but sounds for other functions, replace the speedo/tach
                module.
            </para>
            <para>If the alarm does not sound for any function, replace the alarm.</para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
